---
/**
 * context-engineering 0006 · Figure 1 — the hero "measure the two halves
 * separately" (retrieval half · generation half · tracing underneath).
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from
 * docs/context-engineering/lessons/0006-retrieval-evaluation-and-observability.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption incl. the footnote <sup>). It lives as an .astro
 * component, NOT inline in the MDX, because MDX's JSX parser is unreliable with
 * raw inline SVG that uses kebab-case attributes (text-anchor, font-size,
 * stroke-width, marker-end, …). In an .astro file the SVG is plain HTML, so it
 * renders byte-for-byte.
 *
 * The source page defined the arrowhead markers ONCE in a shared <defs> block at
 * the top of the document <body> (ids: arw, arwG, arwR, arwM). The MDX has no
 * such shared block, so the markers this figure references (arw) are inlined into
 * its own <defs>.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 270"
        role="img"
        aria-label="A pipeline split into a retrieval half and a generation half, each with its own metrics and a tracing layer underneath."
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arw"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#6b675f"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <text x="320" y="18" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11.5" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >MEASURE THE TWO HALVES SEPARATELY</text
        >
        <!-- query -->
        <rect x="26" y="36" width="92" height="40" rx="8" fill="#f1eef2" stroke="#b5179e"></rect>
        <text x="72" y="61" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >Query</text
        >
        <!-- retrieval half -->
        <rect
            x="146"
            y="30"
            width="200"
            height="120"
            rx="10"
            fill="#eef2f7"
            stroke="#1f3a5a"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="246" y="50" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" font-weight="700" fill="#1f3a5a"
            >Retrieval</text
        >
        <text x="246" y="70" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
            >did we even fetch the right doc?</text
        >
        <rect x="162" y="82" width="168" height="54" rx="6" fill="#ffffff" stroke="#1f3a5a"></rect>
        <text x="246" y="100" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >recall@k · precision@k</text
        >
        <text x="246" y="116" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >MRR · nDCG</text
        >
        <text x="246" y="130" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" font-style="italic" fill="#1f3a5a"
            >if recall is bad, no model saves you</text
        >
        <!-- generation half -->
        <rect
            x="374"
            y="30"
            width="200"
            height="120"
            rx="10"
            fill="#f6eef7"
            stroke="#b5179e"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="474" y="50" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" font-weight="700" fill="#b5179e"
            >Generation</text
        >
        <text x="474" y="70" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
            >did the answer use it well?</text
        >
        <rect x="390" y="82" width="168" height="54" rx="6" fill="#ffffff" stroke="#b5179e"></rect>
        <text x="474" y="100" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >faithfulness · relevance</text
        >
        <text x="474" y="116" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >context precision/recall</text
        >
        <text x="474" y="130" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" font-style="italic" fill="#b5179e"
            >grounded in the retrieved context?</text
        >
        <!-- flow arrows -->
        <line x1="118" y1="56" x2="144" y2="56" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <line x1="346" y1="90" x2="372" y2="90" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <!-- tracing layer -->
        <rect
            x="146"
            y="170"
            width="428"
            height="50"
            rx="10"
            fill="#efe7f0"
            stroke="#111110"
            stroke-dasharray="4 3"></rect>
        <text x="360" y="190" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >Tracing — log query · retrieved IDs+scores · packed chunks · answer</text
        >
        <text x="360" y="206" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
            >turns "the bot was wrong" into "doc X wasn't retrieved"</text
        >
        <line x1="246" y1="150" x2="246" y2="168" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <line x1="474" y1="150" x2="474" y2="168" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        One number for the whole system hides where it broke. <b>Split the pipeline:</b> retrieval metrics
        ask "did we fetch it?", answer metrics ask "did we use it?", and tracing underneath tells you
        which half to fix.<sup><a href="#s1" id="r1b">1</a></sup>
    </figcaption>
</figure>
